entries.femaleVariant: "The dame disappeared into the guts of a building ready to collapse. The air hung heavy with smog and betrayal."
'Ey, careful! You'll tear my shirt!
Well, well, well.
Hey, you! What're you doing here?!
Fuck, Cynthia! Told ya to make sure nobody followed you!
I asked what you're doing! Who the hell are you?!
Go on – let's hear it.
It's not me you should be explaining yourself to.
Go on, then. Let's hear it.
It's not me you should be explaining yourself to.
No, no, no, no, wait! Please, please just hear me out!
Job's done. Followed your wife. Went into some run-down pad. Man was waiting for her inside.
She was at a ripper's, gettin' a scan. Her skin, hair, eyes... it's all implanted, every single last part of her.
I'm not gettin' dragged further into this. She'll tell you herself.
She loves you, you gonk.
You're right.
OK – yes, Cynthia was hiding something from you. Yes, she lied, but...
You've got a right to feel cheated, sorta...
entries.maleVariant: You got a right to feal cheated, sorta…

entries.femaleVariant: She was seeing a ripper.
I'm done with this. She'll tell you herself.
I know I should've told Pepe about all this, but... there was never a good time! And... and now that I'm expecting again... Oh, it... It-- it wasn't... It wasn't planned...
Oh, hi. It's, uh, Cynthia, Pepe's wife? Remember me?
Hi, it's Cynthia, Pepe's wife. Remember me?
Uh-huh. I do.
I knew it. What else?
So my son – that's why he...?
Ugh... Maybe it's a good thing I'm dyin'.
Your husband sent me.
Doesn't matter. I've seen enough.
Husband sent me. Suspected something. See he was right.
But... huh? What the hell is going on?!
"They say lies have short legs. But liars – oh, their gams go all the way up."
Oh-ho. Where's this scop coming from?
What? Wait – no! It's... It's not like that! I... I can explain!
Doesn't matter. Seen enough.
"I left her standing there, indifferent to her pleas. The colors of the neon-lit sky played on my retina..."
Dude, just stop already, OK? Seriously.
OK, for-- for one thing... He's not my input – he's my ripper, a specialist in plastic surgery.
A specialist? In this dump?
Look, I know. I... I had this little accident a few year ago. The victim, uh... Well, the patient's family still can't let it go. That's why I'm forced to work here.
Hold on a sec... What about your kid?
Here's the thing... I... Ugh. I didn't used to look like this. I had a total bodysculpt – skin, hair, eyes, everything... except, well, you can't fool your genes.
But... why? Why do that?
Why'd you change your look?
That changes things.
And why do you think? Out of boredom? 'Cause I was a rich, basic bitch?
Everyone's got their own secret. Something they wanna forget, or leave behind them.
Well, uh... Plot's thicker than I imagined, for sure.
I'm glad you listened – saw it from my point of view.
Please... Uh, tell him... Tell him that...
I don't know. I don't know what to tell him myself. That-- that I'm really sorry. That life's an absurdist drama, OK? Just... just go.
Yes?
Hit the nail on the head with that last point.
Dunno. Honestly, don't care, either.
Did my job, now your turn. Waitin' on that scratch.
You know, I thought I'd be more than just one of your regular clients, but I guess I was wrong.
See ya around, V.
Knew it, huh? Didn't know a thing. Didn't cheat on you. Least, not in the way you think.
Huh? What way, then?
Exactly.
Jesus fucking Christo... How could she keep this from me? Her own husband – ten fucking years!
It's not about the skin, or... whatever. It's that she lied. How the hell am I s'posed trust her now?
Not my problem.
Not my biz.
If I were you, I'd just live and let live, y'know?
Yeah... Yeah, I guess you're right.
Good man, Pepe. Take care.
"Silence fell like a wet blanket over the city, muffling its cries. Time to rest, I thought. Time to drink."
OK... What now?
I wish I knew, Pepe. I really do. But who am I to make your mind up for you?
entries.maleVariant: I wish I knew, Pepe. I really do. But who am I to make your mind up for ya?

entries.femaleVariant: Yeah, yeah, I know. Well... see you.
See, that's more like it. Finally makin' some sense.
entries.maleVariant: See? That's more like it. Finally makin' some sense.

entries.femaleVariant: I don't know what you told him, but... thanks. Thank you so much.
Anyway, I guess it was just another day in the life for you. And me? Well, it was the end of mine.
Pepe threw me out. I'm out on the street. I hope – I just hope you're proud of yourself.
That's why our son looks different than Pepe imagined. It's not because he's not the father, just that I... I don't look anything like the old me.
I... I had a lot of 'em. And I can't share them with anyone. Not even my own husband.
The woman loves you, ya gonk. You know how much that means in this fuckin' town?
entries.maleVariant: The woman loves you, ya gonk. Know how much that means in this fuckin' town?

entries.femaleVariant: Anyway, thanks. This is for you... For your troubles.
Oh, right, uh... somethin' for you. Guess you... Guess you earned it.
